I CAN’T thank you all enough for what this year has meant for me, in my personal and professional life. Your support, your trust your love has given me everything and more I thought I could have, so I’m forever grateful for each one of you that keeps following my steps and supporting me along the way. It’s gonna be hard to top this past year, but I’m here and I’m more ready than never. Let’s take each day as a new beginning, every morning as a fresh start, to be better and to do better than the day before, we have 365 opportunities don’t be harsh on you, but don’t waste whats given to you! Happy new year to all wish you all the love and health.

⚠️CHARITY AUCTION TO HELP RESCUE DOGS! ⚠️
I am auctioning one of my micro pet portrait tattoos (single needle, single portrait, black and white no bigger than 3inches)
All proceeds will go to @roadogs. They are a nonprofit organization that saves the lives of medical and disabled underdogs in SoCal.  

 Here are the rules and guidelines.
🐕
1️⃣ Bidding Starts today Friday July 14th
2️⃣ Ends Friday 21st at 11pm
3️⃣ Increments of $20
4️⃣ TAG the person you out bid in you bid comment
5️⃣ Put your bid under “BID HERE” pinned comment
🐕‍🦺

For more info on Roadogs or if you’d like to just donate to help, you can check them out at https://www.roadogs.org/.  Any donations help!  Please like and share to get the word out! Let’s help some dogs!  Winner can send payment directly to Roadogs through paypal, venmo or their website. Then DM proof of payment to set up appointment.

This piece represents the different stages of an artists journey daring to dream while moving from a different country to Hollywood “the land of dreams” in three different layers. 

The first bottom layer represents the initial struggle, the hunger and pain that you face when you first arrive in Hollywood, a place that can quickly make you feel pushed into a corner and filled with self doubt because of big corporations, gate keepers, cost of living and pessimistic mindsets.

The second layer represents a glimmer of hope and a moment of clarity that arrives once you find and you surround yourself with the right people. Ones who believe in and motivate you. Ones that give you the confidence and push to fulfill your dreams. 

The third and final layer represents the most exciting and awaited part of the whole journey, the breakthrough, a layer of joy and light at the end of the tunnel, something not everyone gets to see. This layer represents the sweet taste of achievement that comes from hard work, sacrifices and commitment. The part that I feel, once you reach, is important to send the knowledge you’ve gained along the way back down to the next generation to help others build a roadmap and catch a glimpse of light at the end of the tunnel because the journey as an artist of any sort, is unique in that there is no oversight except that of the public eye, and no traditional path to success either in front of or behind the scenes. My goals with this piece is to shine a light on the many layers of the artist journey in the city of dreams, offer a glimmer of hope and to encourage you and challenge you TO DREAM.
